The paper deals with the problem of partitioning a community into stable groups, which is a classic problem in game theory and social choice theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also deals with network analysis and community detection, which are common topics in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Economic Networks). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning).
